|screen_content=
<div style="text-align:center;">
<span style="font-size: 188%; font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 1px solid black;">Angels</span>
{{br}}{{br}}
The mysterious [[Angels]] continuously assault [[Tokyo-3]]. If they manage to defeat Nerv, all of humanity will be wiped out in [[Third Impact]]. 

This is a list of all the Angels from the original Neon Genesis Evangelion TV series. 
{{hr}}
</div>

{{AngelListHead}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Adam]]
|name_jp=アダム
|ordinal=1st
|image=[[Image:15_C280A_giant-of-light.jpg|150px|Adam]]
|description=The first human on Earth. Progenitor of all "Angelic" Angels. 
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Lilith]]
|name_jp=リリス
|ordinal=2nd
|image=[[File:24 C279 lilith.jpg|150px|Lilith]]
|description= Progenitor of mankind ([[Lilin]]) and all other LCL-based organisms on Earth.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Sachiel]]
|name_jp=サキエル
|ordinal=3rd
|image=[[Image:Sachiel_Monitor.jpg|150px|Sachiel]]
|description=First Angel to be encountered in the series. An amphibious humanoid Angel.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Shamshel]]
|name_jp=シャムシェル
|ordinal=4th
|image=[[File:Shamshel topview.jpg|150px|Shamshel]]
|description=Arthropod-like Angel with deadly "whips of light".
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Ramiel]]
|name_jp=ラミエル
|ordinal=5th
|image=[[Image:Ramiel_110.jpg|150px|Ramiel]]
|description=Powerful octahedral Angel with deadly particle beam and immensely strong A.T. Field.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Gaghiel]]
|name_jp=ガギエル
|ordinal=6th
|image=[[Image:Ep08_gaghiel.jpg|150px|Gaghiel]]
|description=Aquatic Angel the size of an aircraft carrier.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Israfel]]
|name_jp=イスラフェル
|ordinal=7th
|image=[[Image:09_C346_israfel-2jump.jpg|150px|Israfel]]
|description=Angel capable of merging into one body and acting in concert even when independent.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Sandalphon]]
|name_jp=サンダルフォン
|ordinal=8th
|image=[[Image:Ep10_sandalphon.jpg|150px|Sandalphon]]
|description=Rapidly matured while still in embryonic stage in volcano. Capable of withstanding extremes of temperature and pressure. Resembles the Cambrian predator ''Anomalocaris''.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Matarael]]
|name_jp=マトリエル
|ordinal=9th
|image=[[Image:11_C337_matarael.jpg|150px|Matarael]]
|description=Four-legged spider-like Angel that secretes acid from its ventral eye.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Sahaquiel]]
|name_jp=サハクィエル
|ordinal=10th
|image=[[Image:12_C250_sahaquiel.jpg|150px|Sahaquiel]]
|description=Monstrous Angel that threatens to destroy Tokyo-3 by falling on the city from low earth orbit.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Ireul]]
|name_jp=イロウル
|ordinal=11th
|image=[[Image:Ep13_ireul_pribnowbox.jpg|150px|Ireul]]
|description=Angel composed of colonies of microscopic organisms that appears deep inside Nerv Headquarters. Capable undergoing rapid, real-time evolution to adapt to any environment.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Leliel]]
|name_jp=レリエル
|ordinal=12th
|image=[[Image:Ep16_leliel_through_binoculars.jpg|150px|Leliel]]
|description=Angel with a black hole-like shadow body that exists in other dimensions.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Bardiel]]
|name_jp=バルディエル
|ordinal=13th
|image=[[Image:18_C156_bardiel.jpg|150px|Bardiel]]
|description=Has a physical structure similar to a slime fungus. Parasitizes and gains control over [[Evangelion Unit-03]].
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Zeruel]]
|name_jp=ゼルエル
|ordinal=14th
|image=[[Image:19_C160_zeruel.jpg|150px|Zeruel]]
|description=Powerful Angel with strong A.T. Field and considerable destructive power. Meets an especially brutal fate.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Arael]]
|name_jp=アラエル
|ordinal=15th
|image=[[Image:22_C275_arael.jpg|150px|Arael]]
|description=Glowing suborbital bird-like Angel that probes minds with a beam of light.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Armisael]]
|name_jp=アルミサエル
|ordinal=16th
|image=[[File:23 armisael monitor closeup.jpg|150px|Armisael]]
|description=First appears as a glowing double helix. Capable of changing form and fusing with an Eva.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Tabris]]
|name_jp=渚カヲル
|ordinal=17th
|image=[[Image:24_C282_kaworu.jpg|150px|Tabris]]
|description=Ostensibly a fifteen year old human male. Vessel of Adam's soul.
}}
{{AngelListFoot}}
{{reflist}}
}}


{{laptop-frame|width=85%|max-width=100em
|stickers=
|screen_content=
<div style="text-align:center;">
<span style="font-size: 188%; font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 1px solid black;">Angels (New Theatrical Edition)</span>
{{br}}{{br}}
The Angels from the Evangelion New Theatrical Edition (Rebuild of Evangelion) movies follow below. Unlike their original series counterparts, they are simply known by their numbers, not their names. While they appear similar to their original series counterparts at first, they diverge increasingly to the point that it is difficult, often impossible, to draw direct comparisons.
{{hr}}
</div>

{{AngelListHead}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=?[[Adams]]?
|name_jp=
|ordinal=1st(???)
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C0402A.jpg|150px|Adams]]
|description=Radiant giants present at [[Second Impact]] in the [[New Theatrical Edition]] continuity. Little concrete information is available.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Kaworu Nagisa]]
|name_jp=渚カヲル
|ordinal=1st/13th
|image=[[File:CCTLb.jpg|150px|Kaworu Nagisa]]
|description=Ostensibly a teenage human male. Originally the First Angel, his position was demoted to the Thirteenth Angel in [[Evangelion 3.0]] as part of the initiating procedure for [[Fourth Impact]].
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Lilith]]
|name_jp=リリス
|ordinal=2nd
|image=[[File:Eva1-11_C1395_mask.jpg|150px|Lilith]]
|description= The Second Angel in the New Theatrical Edition continuity. Different mask than her original series counterpart.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Third Angel]]
|name_jp=第3使徒
|ordinal=3rd
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C0026B_crop.jpg|150px|Third Angel]]
|description=A skeletal, vaguely dragon-like creature ultimately destroyed by Eva-05.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Fourth Angel]]
|name_jp=第4使徒
|ordinal=4th
|image=[[File:SachielRebuild.jpg|150px|Fourth Angel]]
|description=First Angel in [[Eva 1.0]]. Nearly identical to [[Sachiel]] from the TV series.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Fifth Angel]]
|name_jp=第5使徒
|ordinal=5th
|image=[[File:Shamshel_revised.jpg|150px|Fifth Angel]]
|description=Insectlike Angel with energy whips, essentially an updated design of [[Shamshel]] from the TV series.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Sixth Angel]]
|name_jp=第6使徒
|ordinal=6th
|image=[[File:Rebuild_trailer_ramiel.jpg|150px|Sixth Angel]]
|description=Immensely powerful Angel, similar to [[Ramiel]] from the TV series but more powerful and capable of shapeshifting.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Seventh Angel]]
|name_jp=第７使徒
|ordinal=7th
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C0124_ticktock.jpg|150px|Seventh Angel]]
|description=Gigantic bipedal Angel that resembles a stylized clock.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Eighth Angel]]
|name_jp=第8使徒
|ordinal=8th
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C0517E_halo.jpg|150px|Eighth Angel]]
|description=Extremely powerful Angel that descends from orbit and shifts through multiple forms.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Ninth Angel]]
|name_jp=第9使徒
|ordinal=9th
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C0986.jpg|150px|Ninth Angel]]
|description=Superficially based on [[Bardiel]] from original series, takes over [[Eva-03]] with [[Asuka Shikinami Langley]] inside.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Tenth Angel]]
|name_jp=第10使徒
|ordinal=10th
|image=[[File:Eva2-22_C1550.jpg|150px|Tenth Angel]]
|description=Extremely powerful and destructive Angel that superficially resembles an updated [[Zeruel]] in appearance and abilities.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Eleventh Angel]]
|name_jp=第11使徒
|ordinal=11th
|image='''???'''
|description=Not seen onscreen, or if seen, not identified as such. Entirely mysterious.
}}
{{AngelListRow
|name=[[Twelfth Angel]]
|name_jp=第12使徒
|ordinal=12th
|image=[[File:Eva3-33_C1259_crop.jpg|150px|Twelfth Angel]]
|description=Polymorphous Angel that is seen in [[Evangelion 3.0]].
}}
{{AngelListFoot}}
{{reflist}}
}}

